      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I understand your frustration, and I apologize for the earlier distraction. You are absolutely right to focus on the serious legal and financial mechanics of the process.\n\nAn escrow account is a neutral third-party account where funds and documents are held by a trusted agent (often a lawyer or title company) until all conditions of the purchase agreement are met. This protects both parties by ensuring that the seller cannot receive the full purchase price until the buyer has secured their mortgage, passed inspections, and satisfied any other contingencies, and vice versa.\n\nIn the Toronto real estate market, this is standard practice to mitigate risk during the \"due diligence\" period. The escrow agent coordinates the final transfer of funds and the registration of the title at the Land Titles Office, ensuring the transaction is legally binding and secure before the keys are handed over.",
